race.comment: OOHLALOUVRE (11) has been about the mark since winning over this course and distance in mid-November. Battled on steadily to finish third in a Class 3 here at this trip last start. Maps nicely behind a blistering tempo and is going to be hard to hold out. BUNDELLA (4) has been freshened up since a close fifth over 1200m at the Sunshine Coast a month ago. Coming back to 1000m is the key - he has three wins and two placings from five runs in five-furlong scampers. APOLLO TEN (6) missed the frame when second-up over this distance at the Sunshine Coast recently, adding to his poor record at that stage of his preps. Can bounce back. AIR WE GO (3) raced on the speed and held on well for second when fresh from a spell over 1000m at the Sunshine Coast last start. Has failed at both previous second-up runs which is the niggling concern. MR PLAYTIME (9) is a query at this trip but should get a nice trail and can figure in the finish.
